prompts:
USAV indoor overlap check in a 5–1. Our rotation order clockwise from RB is: (1) RB Setter #12, (2) RF Opposite #7, (3) MF Middle #9, (4) LF Outside #3, (5) LB Libero #2 (for Middle #8), (6) MB Outside #22. In serve receive for this rotation, we stack left:
- #12 (S) starts on the 3 m line between zones 2–3 to run to the net;
- #7 (OPP) is deep in zone 1 near the right corner;
- #9 (MB) is near the center of zone 3;
- #3 (OH) is wide in zone 4 just behind the 3 m line;
- #2 (L) is deep in zone 5;
- #22 (OH) is in zone 6 a step to the right of the libero.
At the moment of serve, is this legal alignment, or is there an overlap fault? If illegal, who is out of order and what small adjustment would fix it?
